<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-31T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="97" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Air Armaments/67:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the American Delegation
                                        (<persName corresp="#p_GHS1" type="from">Gibson</persName>)
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-31T22:00:00+01:00">May
                                        31, 1932—10 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 31—9:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>224. In connection with the work of the Air Commission it is quite
                                likely that proposals will be presented respecting adoption of rules
                                to control aerial warfare. In view of this we would appreciate
                                learning from Department whether report of the Commission of Jurists
                                which met at The Hague in 1923<note n="24" xml:id="d97fn24">
                                    <ref target="frus1923v01#pg_67">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1923, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 67</ref>.</note> constitutes
                                a satisfactory basis for elaboration of such rules and if so would
                                appreciate by mail any detailed suggestions with respect to this
                                report.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GHS1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>